Uganda, Tanzania Sign Agreement to Develop Hydropower Project Along Border

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-09-13T03:32:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/uganda-tanzania-sign-accord-to-develop-hydropower-project.html
Uganda and Tanzania signed an
accord to develop the 16-megawatt Kikagati-Murongo hydropower
project, the  East African Community  said.  In terms of the agreement, two plants will be built on the
Kagera River on the East African nationsâ€™ border, the Arusha,
Tanzania-based organization said in an e-mailed statement today.
The project will be implemented by an independent power
produceer and provide electricity to Kikagati in Uganda and
Murongo in Tanzania, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
